bti
------------------------------------------
Allows you to pipe your bash input to twitter in an easy and fast manner to
annoy the whole world.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.4.12-3
  cygwin-3.3.2-1
  libcurl4-7.80.0-1
  libjson-c2-0.12-1
  liboauth0-1.0.3-1
  libpcre1-8.45-1
  libxml2-2.9.10-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.37-2
  cygport-0.34.0-1
  gcc-core-11.2.0-1
  libcurl-devel-7.80.0-1
  libjson-c-devel-0.12-1
  liboauth-devel-1.0.3-1
  libpcre-devel-8.45-1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.10-2
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/gregkh/bti

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/gregkh/bti/archive/refs/tags/034.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack bti-034-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./bti-034-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/bti-034-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/bti-034-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(bti)
  /etc/bash_completion.d/bti-bashcompletion
  /usr/bin/bti-shrink-urls
  /usr/bin/bti.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/bti.README
  /usr/share/doc/bti/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/bti/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/bti/HACKING
  /usr/share/doc/bti/README
  /usr/share/doc/bti/RELEASE-NOTES
  /usr/share/man/man1/bti-shrink-urls.1.gz
  /usr/share/man/man1/bti.1.gz

